---
source: crates/egui_mcp/src/tools.rs
expression: surface
---
# Server instructions

This mcp drives a live egui app: it reads the app's accessibility tree and synthesizes real input events. Work in an observe → act → verify loop.

Getting oriented:
- Call `attach` first (check `status` if unsure); the app-driving tools return "no app connected" until then.
- Start most tasks with `query_tree` to discover widgets and their ids, and/or `screenshot` to see the rendered frame.

Targeting widgets:
- Prefer locators — an `id` from `query_tree`, or `role`/`label_contains` — over a raw `pos`. Locators resolve to the widget's current position and survive layout changes; reach for `pos` only when nothing matches.
- A locator in an action must match exactly one node. If `role`/`label_contains` matches several, the call errors and lists the candidates — narrow the filter or target a specific `id`. Use `query_tree` when you want every match.

Acting and verifying:
- After an action that changes the UI, confirm it landed: `query_tree` for the expected state, `screenshot` to look, or `wait_for` to poll until async or animated UI settles.
- Use `batch` to act and observe in one round trip (e.g. `click` then `screenshot`), avoiding an extra turn.

Conventions:
- Everything is in logical points, one shared coordinate frame: raw `pos`, `resize` dimensions, the `bounds` from `query_tree`/`get_node`, and a default (`pixels_per_point: 1.0`) `screenshot`. So a node's `bounds` center is exactly where to `click`, and a pixel in the screenshot is a logical point. There is no fixed screen size; use `resize` to set the viewport.

# Tools

## attach

{
  "name": "attach",
  "description": "Connect to a running egui app's inspection port (an app built with eframe's `inspection` feature, launched with `EGUI_INSPECTION` set).\nDefaults to 127.0.0.1:5719.\nRetries until `timeout_secs` elapses.\nOn success the app-driving tools start working (they are always listed, but error until an app is attached).",
  "inputSchema": {
    "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
    "properties": {
      "host": {
        "default": "127.0.0.1",
        "description": "Host the app's inspection port is on.\nDefaults to `127.0.0.1`.",
        "type": "string"
      },
      "port": {
        "default": 5719,
        "description": "Port the app is listening on.\nDefaults to `5719` (`egui_inspection`'s default).",
        "format": "uint16",
        "maximum": 65535,
        "minimum": 0,
        "type": "integer"
      },
      "timeout_secs": {
        "default": null,
        "description": "How long to keep retrying the connection, in seconds.\nDefaults to 10.",
        "format": "uint64",
        "minimum": 0,
        "type": [
          "integer",
          "null"
        ]
      }
    },
    "title": "AttachArgs",
    "type": "object"
  }
}

## batch

{
  "name": "batch",
  "description": "Execute a sequence of app-driving tool calls in one round trip (the connection tools `attach`/`disconnect`/`status` are not available here).\nStops on the first error.\nResults are emitted in execution order, interleaved: each step contributes one JSON text item followed by any image items it produced (e.g. screenshots).\n`batch` cannot be nested.\nUse this to act and observe in one call, e.g. a `click` then a `query_tree` or `screenshot`.",
  "inputSchema": {
    "$defs": {
      "BatchAction": {
        "properties": {
          "args": {
            "additionalProperties": true,
            "default": null,
            "type": "object"
          },
          "name": {
            "type": "string"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "name"
        ],
        "type": "object"
      }
    },
    "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
    "properties": {
      "actions": {
        "items": {
          "$ref": "#/$defs/BatchAction"
        },
        "type": "array"
      }
    },
    "required": [
      "actions"
    ],
    "title": "BatchArgs",
    "type": "object"
  }
}

## click

{
  "name": "click",
  "description": "Click the center of a node's bounding box, or a raw `pos` in logical points.\nSpecify either a locator (`id` from `query_tree` or `role`/`label_contains`) or `pos: { x, y }`.\n`button` defaults to `primary` (accepts `primary`/`secondary`/`middle`/`extra1`/`extra2`, or aliases `left`/`right`).\n`count: 2` → double-click, `3` → triple.",
  "inputSchema": {
    "$defs": {
      "Pos2Lit": {
        "properties": {
          "x": {
            "format": "float",
            "type": "number"
          },
          "y": {
            "format": "float",
            "type": "number"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "x",
          "y"
        ],
        "type": "object"
      },
      "PressKeyModifiers": {
        "properties": {
          "alt": {
            "default": false,
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "command": {
            "default": false,
            "description": "= Cmd on Mac / Ctrl on Win+Linux.",
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "ctrl": {
            "default": false,
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "mac_cmd": {
            "default": false,
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "shift": {
            "default": false,
            "type": "boolean"
          }
        },
        "type": "object"
      }
    },
    "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
    "properties": {
      "button": {
        "default": "primary",
        "description": "`primary`/`secondary`/`middle`/`extra1`/`extra2` (or aliases `left`/`right`).",
        "type": "string"
      },
      "count": {
        "default": 1,
        "description": "`2` → double-click; `3` → triple-click.",
        "format": "uint32",
        "minimum": 0,
        "type": "integer"
      },
      "id": {
        "default": null,
        "description": "Node id from `query_tree`.",
        "type": [
          "string",
          "null"
        ]
      },
      "label_contains": {
        "default": null,
        "type": [
          "string",
          "null"
        ]
      },
      "modifiers": {
        "$ref": "#/$defs/PressKeyModifiers"
      },
      "pos": {
        "anyOf": [
          {
            "$ref": "#/$defs/Pos2Lit"
          },
          {
            "type": "null"
          }
        ],
        "description": "Raw position in logical points (use instead of locator fields)."
      },
      "role": {
        "default": null,
        "description": "Role name, e.g. `Button`, `Label`, `TextInput` (case-insensitive).\nAn unrecognized role errors with the roles present in the tree.",
        "type": [
          "string",
          "null"
        ]
      }
    },
    "title": "ClickArgs",
    "type": "object"
  }
}

## disconnect

{
  "name": "disconnect",
  "description": "Disconnect from the attached app.\nApp-driving tools remain available but return an error until `attach` is called again.",
  "inputSchema": {
    "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
    "title": "EmptyArgs",
    "type": "object"
  }
}

## drag

{
  "name": "drag",
  "description": "Primary-button drag from `start` to `end`.\nEach target accepts the same fields as `click`: locator (`id`/`role`/`label_contains`) or `pos: {x, y}`.\n`steps` controls how many intermediate pointer-move events are emitted between press and release.",
  "inputSchema": {
    "$defs": {
      "Pos2Lit": {
        "properties": {
          "x": {
            "format": "float",
            "type": "number"
          },
          "y": {
            "format": "float",
            "type": "number"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "x",
          "y"
        ],
        "type": "object"
      },
      "PressKeyModifiers": {
        "properties": {
          "alt": {
            "default": false,
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "command": {
            "default": false,
            "description": "= Cmd on Mac / Ctrl on Win+Linux.",
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "ctrl": {
            "default": false,
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "mac_cmd": {
            "default": false,
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "shift": {
            "default": false,
            "type": "boolean"
          }
        },
        "type": "object"
      },
      "Target": {
        "properties": {
          "id": {
            "default": null,
            "description": "Node id from `query_tree`.",
            "type": [
              "string",
              "null"
            ]
          },
          "label_contains": {
            "default": null,
            "type": [
              "string",
              "null"
            ]
          },
          "pos": {
            "anyOf": [
              {
                "$ref": "#/$defs/Pos2Lit"
              },
              {
                "type": "null"
              }
            ],
            "description": "Raw position in logical points (use instead of locator fields)."
          },
          "role": {
            "default": null,
            "description": "Role name, e.g. `Button`, `Label`, `TextInput` (case-insensitive).\nAn unrecognized role errors with the roles present in the tree.",
            "type": [
              "string",
              "null"
            ]
          }
        },
        "type": "object"
      }
    },
    "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
    "properties": {
      "end": {
        "$ref": "#/$defs/Target"
      },
      "modifiers": {
        "$ref": "#/$defs/PressKeyModifiers"
      },
      "start": {
        "$ref": "#/$defs/Target"
      },
      "steps": {
        "default": 8,
        "format": "uint32",
        "minimum": 0,
        "type": "integer"
      }
    },
    "required": [
      "start",
      "end"
    ],
    "title": "DragArgs",
    "type": "object"
  }
}

## get_node

{
  "name": "get_node",
  "description": "Return a single node by id (from `query_tree`).",
  "inputSchema": {
    "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
    "properties": {
      "id": {
        "type": "string"
      }
    },
    "required": [
      "id"
    ],
    "title": "GetNodeArgs",
    "type": "object"
  },
  "outputSchema": {
    "$defs": {
      "NodeView": {
        "properties": {
          "bounds": {
            "anyOf": [
              {
                "$ref": "#/$defs/RectF"
              },
              {
                "type": "null"
              }
            ]
          },
          "disabled": {
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "focused": {
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "hidden": {
            "type": "boolean"
          },
          "id": {
            "description": "Node id, used with `click`, `type_text`, and `get_node`.",
            "type": "string"
          },
          "label": {
            "type": [
              "string",
              "null"
            ]
          },
          "parent_id": {
            "type": [
              "string",
              "null"
            ]
          },
          "role": {
            "type": "string"
          },
          "value": {
            "type": [
              "string",
              "null"
            ]
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "id",
          "role",
          "focused",
          "disabled",
          "hidden"
        ],
        "type": "object"
      },
      "RectF": {
        "properties": {
          "h": {
            "format": "double",
            "type": "number"
          },
          "w": {
            "format": "double",
            "type": "number"
          },
          "x": {
            "format": "double",
            "type": "number"
          },
          "y": {
            "format": "double",
            "type": "number"
          }
        },
        "required": [
          "x",
          "y",
          "w",
          "h"
        ],
        "type": "object"
      }
    },
    "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
    "description": "`get_node` result: the resolved node, or `null` if the id didn't match.",
    "properties": {
      "node": {
        "anyOf": [
          {
            "$ref": "#/$defs/NodeView"
          },
          {
            "type": "null"
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    "title": "GetNodeResult",
    "type": "object"
  }
}

